\begin_layout Standard
To quantify the combined effect of wealth and consumption on one's status
 or answer the more difficult question of whether a certain level of prosperity
 (or other societal conditions which establish an achievable reference level
 necessary consumption) is required for status consumption to exist, we
 must define what constitutes status in a society.
 Taking cue from the literature on social deference (see Coleman
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "ColemanSocialTheory1990"
literal "true"

\end_inset

