 their model for snob and bandwagon items), we view status as a ranking
 order over the consumers in an economy - so that a consumer achieves status
 utility through consumption by moving herself up in this ranking order
 - determined by wealth and income that is visible to other consumers in
 the economy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The literature on status consumption also suggests that that the fulfilment
 of needs alone cannot offer any ranking or status advantage (see Galbraith
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "GalbraithAffluent"
literal "false"

\end_inset

